messages.content: You are trapped underneath rubble. For a moment, you struggle, but your raw strength stat of 15 allows you to lift the rocks off from yourself, exposing a crumbling ruin of a room. A bit of water is dripping into the room from the rock ceiling and a cracked mirror lays facedown across from you. There are a few other stone fixtures that seem to be designed for things like a bed, but they've crumbled to rocky pieces around you.

“Urhh…”
I’m… fucking dammit, this is…

I stretch my back, powering through the pain.

…Why’s water leaking? Is there rain? I look up at the water.
It just seems to be coming from the rock. You can't see the outside or anything.

Huh. Am I underground, or something?

How the hell did I end up in this situation?

I pick up and stare at the cracked mirror.
A few of it's pieces have fallen out. With your intelligence stat of 12 you should be able to rebuild it, however.
That sounds dumb and like a waste of time. Is there an exit to this room?
You don't see one. Your wisdom stat of 8 is unhelpful on any approaches to locating an exit, or if there even is one.
I keep thinking of it as I idly put the pieces together. I try to cut myself on glass fragments as little as possible, I guess.
You successfully reassemble the picture of a young black-skinned woman with a muscular figure. You are wearing a black and white striped prison jumpsuit with the tag Inmate 063.

Oh, shit, is this jail? Am I in jail? I thought jail would look different.

Also, we talkin’ black as in the darkness of night or black like coffee black, where it’s actually just a very dark tannish brown, that kinda thing.

Wait, shouldn’t I know that already… uh.

Huh.
"Help me! Please!" A voice calls out from behind the rubble.
Oh, there’s more rubble, okay. There’s a guy there?! I lift it off ‘em.
You expose a passage out of the room.
Oh, that’s cool. But no guy? I thought I heard a guy there. I glance back at the mirror and then go into the passage.
The path splits into 2 directions, left and right. You hear more noise from the right.
Well, I head to the right then.
An androgynous looking person with a similar skin tone to yours is trapped underneath rubble in an identical room to yours. ((New channel))

You are trapped underneath rubble. For a moment, you struggle, but your raw strength stat of 11 is not enough to escape. All you can do for now is look around, speak, or move your left arm. A bit of water is dripping into the room from the rock ceiling and a cracked mirror lays facedown across from you. There are a few other stone fixtures that seem to be designed for things like a bed, but they've crumbled to rocky pieces around you.
Ugh... god. Wh-what? Where am I? And... how long have I been here?
I guess it can't be that long, considering the situation... but somehow it feels like I might have been here forever. Maybe that's just the pain across my body talking, though... shit.
After failing with my right hand, I reach up with my left to swipe some of my hair out of my face and glance around to see if anyone is here, or even a sign of anyone.
"H... help?"
My voice comes out in a low rasp, a fact which makes me wince on its own, for some reason.
No one is visible.
Hahaha. I guess there wouldn't be. Not many people visiting... whatever kind of shithole this is. This is more cave than house, at this point.
At least there isn't a bear!!

Maybe this is one of those moments where I would wish that I had paid more attention to my physique in life, but in all honesty, I have no idea how much I did or didn't. Which is... strange. But not what I want to be focusing on right now, either way, whether I can find a way out of this or not.
What do I want to be focusing on?
I suppose... I'd like to live. Is the water invading the room anywhere close enough for me to get a taste?
Sure. You can take some water.
I lap it up, like some kind of cat. It makes me feel a bit sick. Not entirely sure whether that's physical or emotional, though.
What does one even do in a situation like this? Wait? Just wait, forever, for somebody? Anybody?
Well, yes, that sounds right.
"Help!"
I have to cough a few times, but my voice comes out clearer now with the added lubrication.
"Help me! Please!"
No response.
"Ahhhhh... ahahahaha! Cool! That's okay! I know somebody will be along eventually, don't worry. I'm a very hopeful person! I think!"
I say this to nobody, of course.
I lay my head back against the floor, and scratch at my face a bit.
A muscular black woman enters the room. ((New channel))
63's 14 charisma paints a positive first impression, but 64's 17 charisma outdoes this immediately.
“Who’re you.” I cough.
I look up again quickly, which makes my neck sting a little. "Oh, hi! Welcome to my room. Well, I'm just somebody trapped under a pile of rubble, basically. That's who I am."
Oh, right. I lift the rubble off the guy, in the room.
Wow. There goes a pretty major aspect of the identity I just established. That kind of sucks, and as much as I feel freed now, I also feel... newly restricted? Does that make any sense?
Anyways, I pull myself up to my feet unsteadily. It takes a bit, and it hurts like hell, but it's not the worst thing in the world.

I reach out my unhurt hand for a... handshake? High five? I don't really know, and I pull it back again before anything can happen. Trying to pretend I didn't do anything, I start inspecting myself for injuries. "How do I look?"
“Good.” I shake my head. “Fine to me, at least. Any clue what caused this place to start fallin’ apart?”

"Oh, to be honest, I had assumed it was always like this. I mean, I knew the rubble had to be new, but I wasn't really thinking about anything else, haha. You would probably have a better idea than me, really! I'm the one who thought a broken mirror laying on the floor made sense as decor until a moment ago. Not exactly the sharpest knife you can put in your knife block!"
Is that the phrase? I felt a bit stupid saying it out loud. Whatever.
“It’s a shed.” I correct the idiom. Is this guy wearing the same sort of getup I am?
"Oh, yeah, that tracks. Sorry."
Yes.
"I'm glad that I'm alright, anyways. Thanks for the assist. Really, thank you."
"You look fine too, of course."
I inspect her after saying this to check whether it's true or not.
“Had a mirror in my room, too. I assume these are the cells. Basic furniture in ‘em, before everything exploded or whatever.”
Your wisdom stat of 10 has trouble reading into what would socially be defined as 'fine' at the moment.
~~People who be DESPERATE to define wisdom stats~~
Oh. Um, well. That could be bad... I really hope I'm not missing anything. I'm kind of failing at my reciprocal part of the relationship here already.
((IT WOULD BE INSIGHT, WHICH IS WISDOM IIRC))
"That's nice. Are you feeling alright? You haven't been hurt or anything, right?"

“Shit fell on me too, but I’m okay. …Things are weirdly quiet. If we’re inmates, there’d be guards tryna stop us from fleeing in this commotion, right? …Are we the only ones left?” Is there an exit directly out of this room or is it just the path I came from?
Just the path you came from.

Oh, are we prisoners? I didn't see any bars, but I guess that would explain the stone construction of the place. I don't think they generally give dangerous criminals glass mirrors to break into shards, but that just means we're low-level. I would hope so, considering I've never committed a crime in my life, besides being inconsiderate and making people do manual labor for my sake.
"We may be the only people, yes. But if that would make you lonely, I have no problem with looking around a bit."
I know I'm not exactly the ideal company.
“We’ll suffocate or starve eventually if everything’s just caved in on itself.” I mutter. “There’s at least one other way I saw. I’m gonna check it out. You may wanna do the same.”
64's 11 intelligence confirms this fact.
Unclear relevance.
"I'll follow you anywhere you want to go."
“Sure.” I head back to the path split. “What’s your name?” I ask this.
I think about it. "I don't have one. What's yours?"
“Everyone has a name, idiot.” I roll my eyes. “I dunno. I’ve felt off since I woke up. Not sure how I got here. Something to do with crime, I think.”
I look down, suddenly embarrassed. "You're right. Who... what kind of person doesn't have a name? Hehe. It's dumb. Sor- I'm sorry."
I try to think of a name.
Nothing comes to mind, though.
The path splits into 2 directions. Presumably 63 heads down the unexplored one?
Yes, that’s what I was doing, yeah. Because I’ve been to the other places.

The path quickly splits again, but thankfully you don’t need to go down one of the directions. It has fully collapsed in and the corpse of Inmate 062 has been partially crushed to a pulp.

63’s 14 constitution and 64’s 16 constitution are enough to hold back any immediate urge to vomit at this sight.
~~Damn! He ain’t gonna be in CoZ The Hub 2!~~

Ugh. Fuck. That's... disgusting. It pains me to think how close I was to ending up like that myself, if this woman was a bit more innately violent. I really lucked out with her. Not that she doesn't look like she could crush me with rubble if she really wanted to.
I avert my eyes. "So, what do you want to call me?"
“I’d prefer whatever you’re called by everybody else, but if you don’t know that either, that’s pretty strange. We got, uh… numbers. I dunno.” I go in the way not blocked by death.
"You are everybody to me."
I cringe a bit as that comes out of my mouth. It sounds like I'm hitting on her. It is true from my perspective, though, and I'm not sure how I'd go about correcting it, so I hurry past it.
"What, uh, what numbers? I don't have a number. Do I?"
I look at the part where logistically the other person would have a number to confirm I’m not causing a plothole by referencing the concept of 64.
That is indeed their number.

Yeah. I gesture to that. “Seems a little inhumane, but I dunno. It’s a nice number. You can get it just from twos.” That’s a weird thing to say. Oh well.  “You look like a, uh…” Shit. I don’t know if it’d be a boy name or a girl name. Or really what those are. “Four…er. Yeah. Fourier. …It doesn’t matter. We’ll find actual info eventually, probably.”
I have no idea what she's talking about. Is she making a pun calling me a courier? What?? I'm clearly mishearing something.
I couldn't even tell where she was pointing to. Is the number on one of my shoulders? I look down to see what I'm wearing, something I should have done a long time ago.

They arrive at a rock wall. Light shines down from above and a rope ladder is visible at the top to be thrown down. 63’s 13 dexterity and 64’s 16 dexterity should let them climb up without the ladder though.
“…Ugh.” I scowl, and begin to climb.
"Can we... um..."
I really wanted a name... damn...
I hang my head and start climbing behind her.

They reach a garden filled with sunflowers that seem to take their name far too literally, shining light like the sun. They are all facing a large intimidating looking door to nowhere in the middle of the garden marked with the word 'Death'.
There are also 2 other holes like the ones they came from with rope ladders still left up.

"HELLO! IS ANYONE UP THERE?" A woman’s voice from one of the holes.

A man’s voice from the same hole. "YEAH, HELLO? WE COULD REALLY USE SOME HELP, IF YOU WOULD BE SO KIND!"
“Man, what?” I sigh. I let down the ladder for whoever else is down there.
"Wait, are you sure? What if they're... you know..."
I furrow my brow.
“There’s only two. I could take ‘em.”

"You don't even know what they look like! They could be so much stronger than you... how can you just... not... care? You're putting me in danger too, you know! What if they gang up on the weaker one?"
"What if they convince you that I don't deserve..."
"There are so many things that could happen! Is what I'm saying."
"Ugh."
A middle aged white woman and this creature enter the garden. Their numbers are 59 and 60 respectively.

You are trapped underneath rubble. For a moment, you struggle, but your raw strength stat of 14 allows you to lift the rocks off from yourself, exposing a crumbling ruin of a room. A bit of water is dripping into the room from the rock ceiling and a cracked mirror lays facedown across from you. There are a few other stone fixtures that seem to be designed for things like a bed, but they've crumbled to rocky pieces around you.

"-nnnggggbuuuaaaahh."

...

I stand. This place isn't familiar. I've found myself in a bit of a pickle, haven't I?

Oh dear. That's bad. That's really really bad.

Well, first things first, I try to determine if there's any route of escape. That seems important. With the room being so thoroughly dilapidated, it's equally possible for my method of escape to have been blocked with rubble and smashed into a wall.

There is no visible route of escape. You attempt to remember some old wisdom about finding an exit, but unfortunately your wisdom of 12 only assures you that it must exist somewhere in the room for you to have ended up here.

Thankfully, you hear a distant shout of "Is anyone there?"

Oh, that's good! If someone else has found his or herself in this situation, that means I'm not alone.

"Me!" I shout back. "I'm here!"
"Hi! Hello! Please help me! I'm stuck!" The voice is coming from behind the rubble you were just laying in. It should be possible to move it out of the way.

"Oh, of course! Sorry!"

I remove the rubble from where the voice seems to be coming from.
You successfully expose a passageway out of the room.
I exit the room, and try to move closer to the voice.
Your path split 2 ways. The voice seems to be coming from the direction of the right.
I go right. "Hello? Where are you?"
There is a middle aged white woman trapped under stone in a room nearly identical to yours.
I free her! Or at least try, haha.

You are trapped underneath rubble. For a moment, you struggle, but your raw strength stat of 11 is not enough to escape. All you can do for now is look around, speak, or move your left arm. A bit of water is dripping into the room from the rock ceiling and a cracked mirror lays facedown across from you. There are a few other stone fixtures that seem to be designed for things like a bed, but they've crumbled to rocky pieces around you.
Hmm. I try to search my memories for anything tangible to understand why I'm in this concerning position.
Nothing. You can't seem to remember anything at all.
That's very concerning! I attempt to yell out, "is anyone there!?"
"Me!" Someone shouts back. "I'm here!"
"Hi! Hello! Please help me! I'm stuck!"
This creature stumbles into your sight. ((Making a channel give me a second))
59's raw 16 charisma makes her seem very immediately approachable. 60's 12 charisma is not enough to stop his intimidating presence.
"Eek! S-Scary..."

"Oh, am I scary? I'm sorry! I didn't mean to be scary."

Is the woman free yet? I hope I've freed her.
60 is strong enough to free 59 from the rubble.

"O-Oh, I'm very sorry, sir... I'm just easily unsettled." I chuckle.

After being freed, I make sure to examine what clothing I may be wearing, as well as any other notable details about my body.
You are wearing a black and white striped prison jumpsuit with the tag Inmate 059. 60 is wearing a similar outfit with the tag Inmate 060.

"It's not my fault, then? That's good, haha. I suppose it would only make sense for me to be a li'l banged up, with all the everything that's clearly happened here. Might be a bit spookier than I want right now!"
"Oh gosh, are we in, like, prison? Did I commit a crime? Oh no, oh no, oh no..."
"Oh, gosh. Are we?"
A closer inspection of yourself would require the mirror. 59's 12 intelligence and 60's 10 intelligence should be enough to solve it like a puzzle and put it's pieces back into place.

The mirror! That's right! Ahh, silly me...

I run to the mirror and check it!

"I mean, uhhh... I don't seem to remember committing any crimes. Maybe they got the wrong guy? Or if I did commit a crime, maybe it was something not that bad, like littering? ...where are you running?"
I follow this woman over to where she stops.
Are you solving the puzzle together?
"Ohh, the mirror is like one of those jigsaw puzzles. Let's solve it, okay little guy?"

"Oh, you mean those puzzles where all the pieces fit perfectly into each other like puzzle pieces? Yeah, I think I know what you're talking about. Alright, let's do it! I'm getting all fired up now!"

I start on the mirror-puzzle.
You manage to rebuild the mirror. 59 is a middle aged white woman. 60 looks like this.
"Aaah!" I find myself jumping back a little. "Sc- scary. Is that me?"

Nothing about my appearance feels off to me, thankfully. I was worried, for a moment, after running into a big wolf man like that!

"Yes, it's you...but it's okay! You did a really good job with the puzzle, thank you so much!"

"I, ah, thank you! It's good that I did a good job, I think. Now that I know I really am this scary, I can hopefully adjust my behavior so I come off as less scary in the future. Do you have any tips, maybe?"
"Ohh, yes, absolutely! There's lots of things you can do to make yourself cuter. What sorts of clothing do you usually wear, dear?"

"Cuter? Uhhhhh..." I look down at what I'm wearing. "Well, I can't seem to remember right now, sorry. The stress of this all must be getting to me. Black and white stripes wouldn't be a bad bet, considering my current get-up. Doesn't strike me as particularly stylish in this exact moment, though, I must admit."
"Wait, wait. Are you also having trouble remembering things?"
"...Maybe? ...Oh, no, yes. I'm definitely having trouble remembering some certain things."
"*Some certain things*? I can't remember anything at all, personally... May I ask what it is that you *do* remember?"
"Errrrr..." I try to remember what I can remember. "I can remember a lot of words. Like the ones I'm using right now."
"Well, I can too... I more meant, memories of your past. Things like that."

"Memories, you say? It's possible. Give me a moment..." Next, I try to remember my memories. It would be really nice to give this poor woman some assurance, as even if she can't remember anything about herself, establishing some baseline about my past would be enough for her to project herself onto, thus providing comfort. "Agh, jeez. I really can't seem to remember anything on that front. Super, super sorry."
"Ah, nooo... That's a real shame. Oh well... I think we should start looking around. Let's stick together, okay?" I consider putting a hand on the wolf-man's shoulder, but I stop myself.
"Okay! Where should we start looking?"
"I'm not sure!" I look around to see if there are any pathways or directions that one would obviously go in.
The only exit is the passage 60 came from.
"What's back there?" I point to the passage.
"Uhh, just some hallways and the room I came from and all that. Perhaps it would be a good idea to start there? There could be more to explore."
"Yes, definitely! Follow me!" I head out the passage.
"Alrighty!" I do as I'm asked.
The passage splits into 2 directions. 59’s 13 wisdom makes the stunning deduction that 60 definitely remembers which one is the dead end.
"Which one is the dead end?"

"Uhh... why would there be a dead end? I guess the room I came from was a dead end, in a sense." I point in the direction I haven't gone in yet. "I haven't gone that way yet, so I guess its end is comparatively less dead, going off how much I know about it."
"Should- well, do you think we should go that way?"
"Yes! Let's go!" I go.
I go!

The path quickly splits again, but thankfully you don’t need to go down one of the directions. It has fully collapsed in and the corpse of Inmate 061 has partially been crushed to a pulp.

59’s 13 constitution and 60’s 14 constitution are enough to hold back any immediate urge to vomit at this sight.
"Oh, no!" I run towards the crushed corpse and examine it.
"O- oh my God." I stop in my tracks. "Is that-... no, please don't tell me that person is dead?"
"Umm, definitely, yeah." I see if I can make out any details about the body.
It’s an unfamiliar black man.
What do you mean by 'crushed to a pulp'? Can I have more details?

"...Oh my God. Oh my God."

No, no, no, hold it back. This woman needs only assurance. It wouldn't do if she saw you like this. That wouldn't be very reassuring at all.

...

Maybe it's healthier to cry only a little bit? To let her know you're not an unfeeling machine. That seems right.

I cry a little bi-... I bawl, a little bit.
There is blood and gore pouring out from underneath the rock that has crushed the majority of the man’s body.
I consider looking further, but hearing wolf-man's cry, I turn to him. "Hey... It'll be alright! We didn't get crushed, right? We survived! So, it's okay!"
*Snnnnrrrrrf.* "I d- I don't like it, when... when people get killed. It's just not right..."
"Nobody does! That's normal! But we need to stay strong, okay? How are we going to make it through this if we don't stay strong?"

"...Yeah. You're right! You're so right." I wipe my face. "I need to stay strong, for the sake of those we've lost, and all who we may lose on the way." Still crying a little, but that's alright. It'll stop eventually. It's like that saying: you may be acting like a baby, but you have to grow up eventually. I'm sure somebody's said that before.
"Yeah! That's right! For the sake of those we've lost, and all who we may lose on the way, we have to grow up! You can do it!" I pause. "Hey, little guy, I should probably ask... What's your name?"
I blink. "Uhhh... well, now that you're putting it at the forefront like this, I can't seem to remember that either. What *is* my name...?"
"Haha, that's a good point. I guess I can't remember mine, either. Oh, I know! Why don't we come up with new names for ourselves! That'd be fun, right?"
"Coming up with names? Oh, well I don't think I'd be any good at that now... this has all been so stressful, I'll probably come up with something plain silly."
"That's okay! Being silly is okay!"
"Well, alright then! If you insist. I'll keep that in mind. Hmm, what name should I pick..."
"May I go with 'Ruthilia'? You look quite like a Ruthilia to me, if you don't mind me saying."

Does he not get that I wanted us to choose the names for *ourselves*? Ah, geez, how dumb is this guy!? Oh well...I'll play along, I suppose.

"Umm, sure! I guess I'll be Ruthilla." I smile warmly. "For you, umm... How about 'John'?"
"Okay! I guess I'm John now. That works." Probably...
"Yay! Okay, should we get going now, John?"
"Yeah! Let's go, then. No more time to waste."
"Yay!" I go,

They arrive at a rock wall. Light shines down from above and a rope ladder is visible at the top to be thrown down. Ruthilla’s 11 dexterity and John's 12 dexterity don’t seem like enough to climb the wall without the help of the ladder however.
"Oh, deary. This seems like it would be a problem." I scratch my head with a finger.
"HELLO! IS ANYONE UP THERE?" I scream upwards.
"Um-" I clear my throat. "YEAH, HELLO? WE COULD REALLY USE SOME HELP, IF YOU WOULD BE SO KIND!"
The ladder is dropped down by someone at the top.
"Oh, goodie!" I begin climbing.
As do I!

They reach a garden filled with sunflowers that seem to take their name far too literally, shining light like the sun. They are all facing a large intimidating looking door to nowhere in the middle of the garden marked with the word 'Death'. There are also 2 other holes like the one they came from with rope ladders still left up.

In the garden are inmates 63 and 64. 63 is a muscular looking young black woman. 64 is an androgynous looking young black person.
"Hi, new friends! Do you have an information on what this, err, situation is...?"
"Oh, dear, bright in here..." I shield my eyes with a forearm some. "Um- hello!"
((the death of Kuom))
“Oh, shit, it’s a beast. My bad, fours.” I get ready for combat.
I stumble back. "See... see? I told you! That guy could clearly win in a fight! We have to run!"
"The effective combat strategy would have been not letting the f-fucking ladder down... threes."
“Hm. Don’t like that.” I grunt.
"Sorry."
"No, no! John is nice! I know he looks big, and scary, but on the inside, he's actually small, and gentle!"
!!! "Right, right!" Agh, I'm kicking myself! I said I'd make an effort to come off as less intimidating, right? "Sorry! I don't want to fight! Ruthilla's correct! I'm not scary!"
“His name’s *John*?” I smirk. Oh, it’s a guy. Not some kind of weird animal. I guess that makes sense. Maybe.
"You are scary! You're scaring me! Don't lie to us like we won't notice!!"
"You don't get to decide that kind of thing for me like you can, what, control my mind?! That's not how it works!"
I backstep even further.
“Obviously he meant he’s not scary in mannerisms even if his physical presentation is. Which is maybe true.” I sound disappointed.
"Why is he scary? That seems really rude..."

"L- lie!? No, no, I'm not lying, I was just-"

...this one's right. I *was* lying.

"S-sorry! Yes, my name's John, apparently!"
Inmate 57 climbs into the garden. He's a middle aged black man with his hair elegantly styled.

You are trapped underneath rubble. For a moment, you struggle, but your raw strength stat of 10 is not enough to escape. All you can do for now is look around, speak, or move your left arm. A bit of water is dripping into the room from the rock ceiling and a cracked mirror lays facedown across from you. There are a few other stone fixtures that seem to be designed for things like a bed, but they've crumbled to rocky pieces around you.

Ow. This hurts a lot.

Is there anything I can reach with my left arm?
You can reach the mirror.

I grab the mirror, which will likely be invaluable later.

...For now, however, all I do is speak up. 

"Is there anyone there?"
The mirror is cracked and a few of it's pieces have fallen out. Your 13 intelligence may be enough to put it back together while you wait for a response.

Well, it's better than just doing nothing. And if I solve the puzzle, I may just get something to save me.

I attempt to put the mirror back together.
You successfully reassemble the picture of a middle aged black-skinned man with his hair elegantly styled. You are wearing a black and white striped prison jumpsuit with the tag Inmate 057.

Huh. I was arrested? Why would that even be the case? I would never do anything wrong.

Still, however. This does mean I have a goal.

Can I escape this prison without dying?
I speak up again. "Hello? Is anyone there?"
No response.

Da*n. No help from anyone. I suppose I will have to attempt escaping on my own. 

I use the mirror to attempt looking around further using angles and such.
"HELLO?" A voice responds.

Oh, nice. I don't need to exercise my mastery over angles yet.

"Hello! Can you help me?"
No response.
D*rn. I guess they died.

A black woman who seems slightly younger than you enters the room. She has shockingly bright blue hair and aside from her prison uniform with the number 56, she's also wearing expensive looking jewelry in her hair.

You are trapped underneath rubble. For a moment, you struggle, but your raw strength stat of 14 allows you to lift the rocks off from yourself, exposing a crumbling ruin of a room. A bit of water is dripping into the room from the rock ceiling and a cracked mirror lays facedown across from you. There are a few other stone fixtures that seem to be designed for things like a bed, but they've crumbled to rocky pieces around you.

I gasp heavily after clawing my way free. Raw panic is still moving through me like a wild animal. I attempt to ground myself, shivering and shaking. *"W-w-what the fuck...."* I mutter to myself, my first instinct being to stammer and stutter my way through frantic disbelief. As if talking will get me anywhere. That's what I know about myself, from the beginning - the firmly-held trust that talking must get me somewhere.
What does my voice sound like...?
The sound of your own voice can be too easily misleading. That sort of information is best answered by the mirror on the floor.

"Eh..?" I mutter aloud, confused. Why isn't it familiar to me? Why don't I... shouldn't I know the words coming out of my mouth? Shouldn't I know the tenor of my voice? What body is.. what soul is... I begin to whimper like a beaten dog. I'm so scared. I don't understand anything!
I go to the mirror, like that'll save me. I stare at myself in it. The person there, that must be me?
The mirror is cracked and a few of it's pieces have fallen out. Your 10 intelligence tells you fixing this mirror together might take a while.
"Hello? Is anyone there?" You hear a faint voice from nearby.
"H-hello?" I stammer in response.
No response.
"HELLO?" I try and yell louder.
"Hello! Can you help me?" The voice.
What direction is it coming from? I try to move towards it.
It's coming from behind the rubble. Your wisdom stat of 14 helps you realize that the draft you're feeling from the rubble means the exit is probably that way.
I walk towards the rubble.
You've already shown you have the strength to move it out of the way.
I move it out of the way.
A passage out of the room is exposed.
I move through the passage.
It splits into 2 directions. You can hear more noise from the right.
I head towards the right.

You arrive in a room nearly identical to where you started, with a middle aged black man with elegantly styled hair trapped underneath the rubble. He's clutching a fixed mirror in his hand and wearing a black and white striped prison uniform with a tag reading Inmate 057.
56's 13 charisma paints a moderately good first impression. 57's 15 charisma seems very trustworthy.

"Hi there! Could you help me out? I seem to be in a bit of a bind."
